        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 18 at 2:53PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 253 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 5 miles northwest of Agate to 6 miles
north of Strasburg, or extending from 24 miles northwest of Limon to
32 miles east of Denver, moving north at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Deer Trail, Byers, Strasburg and Cottonwood Valley.

This includes Interstate 70 between mile markers 307 and 338.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Heavy rain is occurring with these storms and may lead to flooding.
Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
